            "answer_text": "Globalization from the business perspective can mean the potential of remote talents which can help organizations all over the world from anywhere in the world. Automative sourcing programs can text people who are qualified for jobs and have a conversation through a chatbot and then route them to a recruiter, if qualified. Another advantage of globalization can be specialized jobs, which can be done by people with less experience but more technology. A good example is Khan Academy, which allows laypeople with certain skills and information to share to become teachers, despite possibly having no formal education training. As contractors and freelancers are now very popular, they can be hired for some specific tasks. In this way, it also can be beneficial for business owners. If you want to learn more advantages of globalization for business owners, continue reading this article - Localization to Globalization and Back Again. ",
